02:14.573 --> 02:16.506
<i>The communion of saints...</i>

02:16.573 --> 02:19.904
<i>forgiveness of sins, the
resurrection of the body...</i>

02:19.973 --> 02:21.906
<i>and life everlasting.</i>

02:21.973 --> 02:24.269
<i>Amen.</i>

02:24.339 --> 02:26.330
Let us pray.

02:28.308 --> 02:30.740
Lord, have mercy upon us.

02:30.808 --> 02:32.740
Christ, have mercy upon us.

02:32.809 --> 02:35.138
Lord, have mercy upon us.
Amen.

02:35.209 --> 02:37.402
Our Father.

02:37.475 --> 02:39.703
Our Father, which art
in heaven, hallowed...

02:39.776 --> 02:42.707
Dear God, there's something
I want to ask you.

02:42.775 --> 02:44.707
Of course you know what it is...

02:44.776 --> 02:47.708
because you know everything that's
going to happen before it happens...

02:47.775 --> 02:50.208
so there's really
no need to ask you.

02:50.276 --> 02:52.708
But I thought I'd ask
you in any case.

02:52.776 --> 02:55.209
Now, you know that I believe in you.

02:55.278 --> 02:58.506
But I was wondering if you could
give me just a little sign.

03:04.311 --> 03:07.245
I mean, I'm not saying that if
you don't give me the sign...

03:07.312 --> 03:10.641
that I won't believe in you... I'm not
threatening you or anything like that.

03:10.711 --> 03:13.644
<i>But please, please give
me enough courage...</i>

03:13.712 --> 03:16.769
<i>to speak to Margaret Spencer
and get to know her.</i>

03:16.845 --> 03:19.936
O God, make clean our
hearts within us.

03:20.012 --> 03:22.773
And take not thy
holy spirit from us.

03:27.480 --> 03:29.095
Miss Spencer...

03:29.846 --> 03:32.836
I wonder if I could
have a word with you.

03:32.914 --> 03:34.812
There's something
I've got to tell you...

03:34.881 --> 03:38.142
something I've got to
bring out into the open.

03:38.214 --> 03:40.646
I've been bottling it up
inside me too long...

03:40.714 --> 03:44.339
and there's no point
in hiding it anymore.

03:44.415 --> 03:47.848
For six years now, ever since
you came to Wimpy's...

03:47.916 --> 03:50.780
I've been in love with you.

03:50.848 --> 03:53.644
I only live to hear your voice.

03:53.716 --> 03:57.079
One cheeseburger, one shanty,
one portion french fries.

03:57.150 --> 03:59.082
Each time you speak...

03:59.150 --> 04:03.276
it's like a thousand violins
playing in the halls of heaven.

04:03.350 --> 04:05.317
I-I love you, Miss Spencer.

04:05.384 --> 04:08.611
I love everything about you...

04:08.684 --> 04:13.448
the way you walk, your sweet
smile, your easy grace and charm.

04:13.519 --> 04:17.349
Wimpy Burgers twice, one M.R.,
one well, heavy on the onions.

04:17.418 --> 04:20.942
I wish I could take you
away from all this.

04:21.017 --> 04:23.610
I'd like us to start a
new life together...

04:23.686 --> 04:27.949
a little house of our own, a car,
the two of us against the world...

04:28.019 --> 04:30.814
joined forevermore in holy wedlock.

04:36.969 --> 04:38.147
Miss Spencer!

04:38.281 --> 04:39.647
What?

04:45.059 --> 04:46.697
Nothing.

05:24.325 --> 05:26.258
Good evening.

05:26.326 --> 05:29.017
I couldn't help noticing that you were
making an unsuccessful suicide bid.

05:29.090 --> 05:32.355
What are you doing in my room?
What do you want?
I'm here to help you, Mr. Moon.

05:32.426 --> 05:35.586
- I don't want any help. Please go away.
- Oh, all right.

05:35.659 --> 05:38.956
I just thought you might be interested
in a little matter of a million pounds.

05:39.027 --> 05:40.617
A million pounds?

05:44.094 --> 05:46.524
Don't let me interfere with
your doing away with yourself.

05:46.593 --> 05:48.525
What's this about a million pounds?

05:48.593 --> 05:50.525
- May I come in?
- Yes, please do.

05:50.593 --> 05:53.685
Thank you. I wonder if you'd
mind taking my cloak.

05:54.760 --> 05:57.249
Hang it somewhere dry, would you.

05:58.394 --> 06:00.987
- Might I sit down?
- Oh. Do.

06:01.063 --> 06:02.994
Thank you.

06:03.062 --> 06:06.357
- It's a very nasty little place you've got here.
- Oh. Thank you.

06:06.428 --> 06:08.361
What's this about a million pounds?

06:08.428 --> 06:10.361
Oh, a million pounds, yes.

06:10.428 --> 06:12.487
You remember your
great-great-great-grandfather?

06:12.563 --> 06:14.790
Well, I never even met my father.

06:14.862 --> 06:17.852
- How very sad.
- Excuse me.

06:20.130 --> 06:23.562
In all events, your great-great-great-
grandfather, Ephraim Moon...

06:23.630 --> 06:26.563
sailed for Australia in
1782 on a ship of the line.

06:26.631 --> 06:28.927
Set himself up as an apothecary.

06:28.998 --> 06:30.930
The business flourished...

06:30.998 --> 06:33.931
and by the time he died it was worth
something in the region of £2,000.

06:33.999 --> 06:36.260
A large amount in those days.
Yes.

06:36.331 --> 06:38.763
Your great-great-grandfather,
Cedric Moon...

06:38.832 --> 06:41.264
by skillful management
and careful husbandry...

06:41.331 --> 06:43.265
increased that sum a hundredfold.

06:43.331 --> 06:46.924
This, in turn, was inherited by your
great-grandfather, Desmond Moon...

06:46.999 --> 06:49.261
who expanded, diversified...

06:49.332 --> 06:54.426
and built up a personal fortune
of well over a million pounds.

06:54.500 --> 06:56.329
Oh. That's a lot of money.

06:56.400 --> 06:59.127
A great deal of money, Mr. Moon.

06:59.200 --> 07:01.758
And this gigantic sum...

07:01.834 --> 07:05.096
was inherited by your
grandfather, Hubert Moon...

07:05.168 --> 07:08.930
who returned to London and frittered it
away on wine, women and loose living.

07:11.069 --> 07:13.591
Uh, where does that leave me then?

07:13.668 --> 07:16.897
Penniless and on the
brink of suicide.

07:20.569 --> 07:23.500
You get out of here
before I call the police.

07:23.569 --> 07:25.500
Before you call the what?
The police.

07:25.569 --> 07:28.501
You realize that suicide
is a criminal offense.

07:28.569 --> 07:31.559
In less enlightened times
they'd have hung you for it.

07:33.737 --> 07:35.669
Look, exactly what do you want?

07:35.736 --> 07:38.668
I told you.
Seriously, I want to help you.

07:38.736 --> 07:41.669
Unburden yourself. It does you
good to share your problems.

07:41.737 --> 07:44.670
What interest is it to you?

07:44.738 --> 07:47.899
Please go away!
I'm interested in everybody.

07:47.973 --> 07:51.098
Please tell me. What drove
you to this desperate act?

07:51.173 --> 07:53.605
All right, I'll tell you.
I'm miserable.

07:53.672 --> 07:56.604
I've got a boring job, no
money, no prospects...

07:56.671 --> 08:01.105
I haven't got a girlfriend, I can't get to know
anyone, no one wants to get to know me...

08:01.173 --> 08:03.105
and everything is hopeless.

08:03.173 --> 08:05.105
All right? Satisfied?

08:05.173 --> 08:08.197
And if you really want to help me,
you can get me a sock for this pipe.

08:08.273 --> 08:11.638
Oh, yes. They're in the top
left-hand drawer, aren't they?
Yeah.

08:11.708 --> 08:14.038
But suicide, Mr. Moon?

08:14.108 --> 08:16.039
Really, really, really.

08:16.108 --> 08:18.039
That's the last thing you should do.

08:18.108 --> 08:21.041
Don't you think it's
taking the easy way out?

08:21.108 --> 08:23.041
Easy way out?

08:23.108 --> 08:25.041
What's easy about it?

08:25.108 --> 08:27.540
Look. The bleedin' pipe's broken.

08:27.610 --> 08:29.541
Can't even manage to kill myself.

08:29.610 --> 08:32.539
Let's face it, Mr. Moon...
you're a complete failure.

08:32.607 --> 08:34.940
Yes... Oh.

08:35.010 --> 08:36.943
I'll fix that.

08:37.010 --> 08:39.601
You know that million
pounds I mentioned?

08:39.677 --> 08:41.609
Yes?
I wasn't joking.

08:41.677 --> 08:43.836
I could give you that and more.

08:43.910 --> 08:46.342
Everything you've ever seen
in the advertisements...

08:46.411 --> 08:48.343
fast, white convertibles...

08:48.411 --> 08:51.342
blonde women, their hair
trailing in the wind...

08:51.410 --> 08:53.343
wafer-thin after-dinner chocolates.

08:53.411 --> 08:56.036
If you had all that, would
you be any happier?

08:56.111 --> 08:58.134
What are you on about?

08:58.211 --> 09:01.077
Would the words Prince of
Darkness mean anything to you?

09:01.146 --> 09:04.044
Beelzebub? Mephistopheles?
The horned one?

09:06.246 --> 09:08.178
I know. You've escaped
from somewhere.

09:08.246 --> 09:10.178
No, I haven't, Mr. Moon.

09:10.246 --> 09:13.975
I'm the horned one, the devil.
Let me give you my card.

09:17.247 --> 09:19.542
Oh, yes, the devil. Of course.

09:19.613 --> 09:21.546
Silly old me.

09:21.614 --> 09:24.410
Cor blimey!
I left my hankie at Wimpy's.

09:24.481 --> 09:27.641
I wonder if you'll excuse me.
Don't rush away, Mr. Moon.

09:27.715 --> 09:30.011
You're a nutcase.
You're a bleedin' nutcase.

09:30.082 --> 09:32.809
They said the same of Jesus
Christ, Freud and Galileo.

09:32.881 --> 09:34.848
They said it of a lot
of nutcases too.

09:34.917 --> 09:37.848
You're not as stupid as you
look, are you, Mr. Moon?

09:37.915 --> 09:41.077
What can I do to convince
you that I'm the devil?

09:41.149 --> 09:44.081
Supposing I granted you your
dearest wish here and now?

09:44.149 --> 09:46.272
What about that girl at Wimpy's?

09:46.348 --> 09:48.976
Margaret Spencer?
Yes.

09:49.050 --> 09:50.981
How do you know about her?

09:51.049 --> 09:53.483
And how do you know
so much about me...

09:53.552 --> 09:55.484
where my socks are and
who my grandfather was?

09:55.552 --> 09:58.176
I told you.
I've been taking an interest in you.

09:58.251 --> 10:00.980
Look, well, supposing I, um...

10:01.052 --> 10:02.983
gave you a trial wish.

10:03.051 --> 10:05.482
No obligation on your part.
Just to get acquainted.

10:05.551 --> 10:08.313
Is there anything in the
world you really desire?

10:08.385 --> 10:10.350
Margaret Spen...
Aside from Margaret Spencer.

10:10.418 --> 10:13.009
We'll save her till later, when
you sign. Anything else?

10:13.085 --> 10:17.518
Um... a Frobisher and Gleason
raspberry-flavored ice lolly.

10:17.585 --> 10:19.518
Very well, Mr. Moon.

10:19.586 --> 10:22.882
Conclusively to prove that
I am indeed the unholy one...

10:22.953 --> 10:25.612
a Frobisher and Gleason
raspberry-flavored ice lolly...

10:25.686 --> 10:27.619
shall be yours...

10:27.687 --> 10:29.676
in a trice.

10:36.621 --> 10:39.553
Here you are.
Thank you.

10:39.620 --> 10:41.554
Oh, um, have you got sixpence?

10:41.621 --> 10:44.144
I've only got a million-pound note.

10:44.220 --> 10:46.153
- Thank you.
- Ta.

10:46.221 --> 10:48.711
Convinced?
Do me a favor.

10:48.789 --> 10:50.722
I could have done that myself.

10:50.789 --> 10:52.778
I thought you were
gonna conjure it up.

10:52.856 --> 10:56.448
You're just like all the rest, aren't you?
No proof is good enough.

10:56.523 --> 10:58.545
I want a miracle.

10:58.623 --> 11:00.556
A rain of toads or something.

11:00.624 --> 11:04.055
All right then. Which of the
cheap tricks is it gonna be?

11:04.123 --> 11:06.555
Wine into water?
Stick into serpent?

11:06.624 --> 11:09.455
How about flying through
space at the speed of light?

11:09.524 --> 11:13.047
How about you checking in to the nearest
loony bin for a few weeks' holiday?

11:13.124 --> 11:15.558
O ye of little faith, Moon.

11:15.627 --> 11:17.955
You're not wearing nylon
underwear, are you?

11:18.024 --> 11:20.514
Why?
It disintegrates at high speeds.

11:20.592 --> 11:22.525
Prepare yourself.

11:22.592 --> 11:24.387
The magic words: I.B.J.

11:26.525 --> 11:28.788
Here, my ice lolly's melted.

11:30.193 --> 11:32.125
You really must be the devil.

11:32.193 --> 11:35.182
Incarnate. How do you do?
Oh. How do you do?

11:41.629 --> 11:43.617
Where are we? Is this hell?

11:43.695 --> 11:45.489
Just my London headquarters.

11:46.428 --> 11:48.587
That's not your name, is it?

11:48.662 --> 11:51.628
George Spiggott?

11:51.695 --> 11:54.855
Come on in. It's one of my many
earthly pseudoplumes, or nom de nyms.

11:54.929 --> 11:56.860
I thought you were called Lucifer.

11:56.929 --> 11:59.360
I know. The Bringer of the
Light, it used to be.

11:59.428 --> 12:01.053
Sounded a bit pouffy to me.

12:01.128 --> 12:03.061
God keeps changing his
name too, you know.

12:03.128 --> 12:05.062
He used to be called the Word.

12:05.129 --> 12:08.063
Yeah."ln the beginning was the Word."
"And the Word was God."

12:08.130 --> 12:11.062
Was there just a word
hanging about in space then?
I suppose so.

12:11.129 --> 12:13.062
I wasn't there.

12:13.129 --> 12:15.858
What's it mean,"the Word"?
What does"Stanley Moon" mean?

12:15.931 --> 12:17.920
Evening, Anger.

12:22.531 --> 12:25.463
It's all right, Anger.
He's with me.

12:25.531 --> 12:27.464
Come in, Mr. Moon.

12:27.532 --> 12:30.464
I'd like you to meet Anger.
He works for me.

12:30.532 --> 12:32.690
How do you do?
Pleased to meet you.

12:32.765 --> 12:34.994
Watch it, that's all.

12:37.966 --> 12:39.898
This is the, uh, Club Room.

12:39.966 --> 12:43.797
It's, uh, quite nicely decorated
and painted. Early Hitler.

12:43.867 --> 12:45.799
Now, what about my
little proposition?

12:45.867 --> 12:49.196
All I want from you is something you
probably don't even realize you have.

12:49.267 --> 12:51.199
I'm talking about your soul.

12:51.267 --> 12:53.198
My soul?
Yes.

12:53.267 --> 12:55.199
Like you collect moths...

12:55.268 --> 12:57.200
I collect souls.

12:57.269 --> 13:00.200
I'd like to add yours
to my collection.

13:00.268 --> 13:03.134
What are you doing?
Just a bit of routine mischief.

13:03.202 --> 13:05.168
Now, then, what about your soul?

13:05.236 --> 13:09.565
Well, uh, I don't know where it
is or how to get hold of it.

13:09.636 --> 13:11.568
Exactly.

13:11.636 --> 13:15.694
And all I want from you is the exclusive
global and universal rights to it.

13:16.836 --> 13:18.995
But if you took it
out, wouldn't it hurt?

13:19.069 --> 13:21.002
It's a painless operation.

13:21.070 --> 13:23.468
And afterwards, you
won't feel a thing.

13:23.538 --> 13:25.560
Besides, it's been no earthly
good to you, has it?

13:25.637 --> 13:27.399
Like to look at the contract?
Yes, please.

13:27.470 --> 13:29.404
There we are.

13:29.472 --> 13:33.063
Your soul's rather like your appendix...
totally expendable.

13:33.138 --> 13:35.571
There was a time when it
did have a function...

13:35.639 --> 13:40.071
but nowadays the vast majority
of people never use it.

13:40.138 --> 13:42.571
Looks a bit complicated.

13:42.640 --> 13:44.571
It's a standard contract.

13:44.639 --> 13:47.571
Gives you seven wishes in accordance
with the mystic rules of life...

13:47.638 --> 13:52.072
seven days of the week, seven deadly sins,
seven seas, Seven Brides for Seven Brothers.

13:52.140 --> 13:54.071
Look, if you're not interested...

13:54.140 --> 13:57.130
I'm sure there's thousands of others
who'd jump at the opportunity.

13:58.274 --> 14:00.400
No, it's just a bit
sudden, that's all.

14:00.475 --> 14:03.498
Read it through on your own time.

14:05.574 --> 14:07.506
"I, Stanley Moon...

14:07.574 --> 14:09.507
"hereinafter and in the hereafter...

14:09.575 --> 14:12.166
to be known as the damned..."

14:12.241 --> 14:15.698
The damned?
It's a form of words. Legal jargon.

14:17.310 --> 14:20.706
"Do warrant that I am the
sole owner of my soul."

14:22.577 --> 14:26.304
But what about Margaret? Do you promise
that I'll have her all to myself?

14:26.377 --> 14:28.366
Sign that...

14:29.378 --> 14:31.240
and Margaret Spencer...

14:31.310 --> 14:33.173
will be yours.

14:33.243 --> 14:37.438
"Dear Miss Spencer, this
is just to say cheerio.

14:37.511 --> 14:40.305
"Yours sincerely, Stanley Moon.

14:40.377 --> 14:44.573
P.S. I leave you my
collection of moths."

14:44.646 --> 14:47.076
Just how well did you know Mr. Moon?

14:47.144 --> 14:50.077
Not at all, really.
I used to see him at Wimpy's.

14:50.145 --> 14:53.578
Well, it does seem that, of all the people
in his life, you were the closest to him.

14:53.647 --> 14:57.169
Why else would he leave you that note?
I suppose that must be true.

14:57.245 --> 14:59.837
How awful.

14:59.912 --> 15:03.310
Have you any idea why he
contemplated this rash act?

15:03.380 --> 15:05.312
Can't say, really.

15:05.380 --> 15:08.314
At work he always seems
so calm and quiet.

15:08.382 --> 15:10.314
Sorry to be so blunt,
Miss Spencer...

15:10.382 --> 15:14.337
but are you sure you're not concealing your
relationship with the would-be deceased?

15:14.414 --> 15:17.869
Wasn't a relationship.
I scarcely knew the man.

15:19.481 --> 15:22.141
What are you doing all
that measuring for?

15:22.215 --> 15:25.306
Eh? Oh, we always do
this, Miss Spencer.

15:25.382 --> 15:27.349
You'd be amazed how
often it pays off.

15:27.415 --> 15:30.349
Now, did you say anything
that might have upset him?

15:30.416 --> 15:32.813
Can you remember your
exact last words to him?

15:32.881 --> 15:35.145
I think it was...

15:35.217 --> 15:39.876
"Wimpy Burgers twice, one M.R.,
one well, heavy on the onions."

15:39.949 --> 15:42.747
Yes, I think I'm beginning
to get the picture.

15:44.584 --> 15:47.516
- It all seems to be quite straightforward.
- Good.

15:47.584 --> 15:50.778
All we need do now, then,
is get it witnessed.

15:52.384 --> 15:54.815
Sloth would be best. He's a lawyer.

16:00.785 --> 16:04.684
Come on now, Sloth!
Wake up, you idle, great slob!

16:04.753 --> 16:06.685
Here, are all your staff like this?

16:06.753 --> 16:09.685
That's the trouble. I can't get
any decent help these days.

16:09.752 --> 16:11.685
God's laughing, of course.

16:11.752 --> 16:14.185
All he has to do is raise
his little finger...

16:14.253 --> 16:18.481
he's got a thousand sycophantic,
prissy angels at his beck and call.

16:18.553 --> 16:20.916
I'm lumbered with Anger and Sloth.

16:20.986 --> 16:24.079
Wake up, you lazy, legal layabout!

16:24.154 --> 16:26.746
Get up! Wake up!

16:29.855 --> 16:32.151
Here, well, this is Stanley Moon.

16:32.221 --> 16:36.155
He's selling me his soul, and I want
you to witness it on this document.

16:36.222 --> 16:38.155
I want you to do some writing.

16:38.222 --> 16:40.348
That's your forte, isn't it?
Writing.

16:40.424 --> 16:43.356
Where it says,"ln the
presence of," your signature.

16:43.425 --> 16:45.356
Your name. Remember that one?

16:45.425 --> 16:48.014
Y... Yeah.
Sloth.

16:48.089 --> 16:50.988
S... I...
S... I...

16:51.057 --> 16:54.252
O... T...
O... T...

16:54.325 --> 16:56.723
T... H.

16:56.792 --> 16:59.951
Right. Very nice.
Now it's your turn.

17:00.024 --> 17:02.288
Um...

17:02.360 --> 17:04.290
there's just one thing, though.

17:04.359 --> 17:06.276
You're not having second
thoughts, are you?

17:06.301 --> 17:10.258
No. But shouldn't I sign in blood?
Blimey, you are a traditionalist.

17:10.327 --> 17:12.258
All right then.

17:12.327 --> 17:14.383
Let's use some of his.
He'll never notice.

17:16.093 --> 17:18.082
There we are. Help yourself.

17:25.859 --> 17:28.884
Well done.
Welcome to the club.

17:28.961 --> 17:32.484
- When can I get started on my wishes?
- Soon as you like.

17:34.294 --> 17:37.228
And if, by any chance,
you become dissatisfied...

17:37.296 --> 17:39.726
all you have to do is go...

17:39.795 --> 17:41.886
Just go...
You just go...

17:41.960 --> 17:45.156
This'll terminate your wish and bring
you back to me, wherever I am.

17:45.229 --> 17:47.161
Here we are. "M."

17:47.229 --> 17:49.162
Let's see, um...

17:49.230 --> 17:53.162
Machiavelli, McCarthy,
Masoch, Miller, Moses...

17:53.230 --> 17:55.753
- Moses?
- Irving Moses, the fruiterer.

17:55.831 --> 17:58.161
Here's Moon. S. Moon.

17:59.663 --> 18:01.527
That's you filed away.

18:01.597 --> 18:04.529
Now then, what would you like
